          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl text-ink mb-4 leading-tight">The brief is the design.</h3>
          <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
            80% of the work is the spec. Once the spec was right, the output was
            90% right on the first try. The traditional design process was mostly
            translation: intent into mocks, mocks into specs, specs into code.
            The brief now does all of that work directly.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="lesson-card">
          <div class="linocut-icon">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
              <circle cx="32" cy="32" r="18" fill="#E13D0F"/>
              <line x1="20" y1="24" x2="44" y2="24" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5"/>
